%20the%20New%20York%20City%20market%20%E2%80%94%20in%20which%20homes%20usually%20just%20get%20more%20expensive%20%E2%80%94%20the%20couple%20decided%20to%20stay%20put.%20But%20they%20wanted%20to%20create%20separate%20sleeping%20spaces%20for%20the%20growing%20child%20and%20the%20two%20working%20parents%2C%20one%20a%20clinical%20psychologist%20and%20one%20an%20occupational%20therapist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnter%20architect%20Robert%20Garneau%2C%20who%20first%20experimented%20with%20flexible%20spaces%20in%20his%20own%20New%20York%20City%20apartment%2025%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20project%20is%20unique%20but%20there's%20a%20way%20of%20thinking%20about%20small%20spaces%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Garneau%2C%20who's%20worked%20on%20over%2050%20projects%20across%20New%20York%20City%2C%20California%2C%20Spain%2C%20and%20France.%20%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20consider%20the%20space%20in%20its%20entirety%2C%20but%20also%20down%20to%20the%20square%20inch%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20everything%20fits%20properly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarneau%20and%20his%20team%20designed%20a%20custom%20space%20for%20the%20family%20that%20allows%20their%20main%20living%20area%20to%20perfectly%20conceal%20another%20bedroom%20%E2%80%94%20thanks%20to%20a%20discreet%20movable%20wall%20and%20Murphy%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20apartment%2C%20located%20on%20Manhattan's%20family-friendly%20Upper%20East%20Side%2C%20clocks%20in%20at%20400%20square%20feet.%20But%20Garneau%20was%20able%20to%20create%20a%20flexible%20space%20%E2%80%94%20which%20functions%20as%20a%20living%20room%20with%20an%20open%20kitchen%2C%20a%20bedroom%2C%20and%20an%20office%20%E2%80%94%20out%20of%20the%20main%20living%20space%2C%20which%20is%20just%20250%20square%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20up%20the%20other%20150%20square%20feet%20is%20the%20hallway%2C%20the%20bathroom%2C%20and%20the%20main%20bedroom%2C%20which%20is%20the%20child's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20which%20first%20profiled%20the%20apartment%2C%20the%20couple%20purchased%20it%20in%202006%20for%20around%20%24300%2C000.%20The%20renovation%20cost%20about%20%24280%2C000%2C%20Garneau%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20has%20now%20lived%20comfortably%20in%20the%20renovated%20apartment%20for%20over%20two%20years%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20take%20a%20look%20inside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20main%20living%20space%20is%20about%20250%20square%20feet.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20living%20space%20of%20the%20apartment%20with%20a%20white%20table%2C%20brown%20leather%20couch%2C%20and%20smooth%2C%20gray%20walls%20with%20patches%20of%20exposed%20brick.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66573b6285e29ef64829cecc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20living%20space%20in%20the%20apartment.%20%3Cp%3EDan%20Latu%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20living%20room%20can%20be%20set%20up%20to%20be%20one%20continuous%2C%20rectangular%20living%20space.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EGarneau%20said%20there's%20a%20'domino%20effect'%20when%20designing%20a%20space%20this%20small.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Robert%20Garneau%20stands%20in%20the%20apartment%20against%20a%20smooth%2C%20gray%20wall.%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66573b61d38d94707c2bfbb5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArchitect%20Robert%20Garneau%20first%20experimented%20with%20movable%20spaces%20with%20his%20own%20New%20York%20apartment%20over%2020%20years%20ago.%3Cp%3EDan%20Latu%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20designing%20a%20small%20space%2C%20Garneau%20recommends%20starting%20with%20the%20main%20components%20of%20the%20room%20and%20then%20carving%20out%20spaces%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20case%2C%20the%20couple%20absolutely%20wanted%20to%20keep%20a%20leather%20couch%20they%20owned%20previously%20and%20make%20enough%20space%20for%20their%20new%20Murphy%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarneau%20and%20his%20team%20used%20those%20items%20as%20a%20starting%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EGarneau%20added%20storage%20despite%20the%20small%20space%20by%20designing%20some%20cabinets%20that%20are%20only%20eight%20inches%20deep.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20view%20of%20the%20wall%20concealing%20cabinets%20and%20a%20bed%20with%20smooth%2C%20gray%20cabinetry.%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66573b62f5084fadb175bd19%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20main%20living%20area%20of%20the%20apartment.%20%3Cp%3EDan%20Latu%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20fun%20in%20small%20spaces%20is%20you%20manage%20to%20carve%20space%20out%20of%20things%20that%20often%20don't%20really%20get%20designed%2C%26quot%3B%20Garneau%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20don't%20typically%20build%20cabinets%20that%20are%20that%20shallow.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20parents%20use%20the%20storage%20in%20the%20main%20living%20room%20as%20their%20closets%20for%20clothes%20and%20personal%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EGarneau%20even%20played%20with%20gradients%20of%20color%20to%20make%20the%20room%20feel%20brighter.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Robert%20Garneau%20stands%20in%20the%20apartment.%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66573b61f5084fadb175bd16%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGarneau%20points%20out%20design%20features%20of%20the%20apartment.%3Cp%3EDan%20Latu%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cabinets%20may%20look%20all%20one%20shade%20of%20gray%2C%20but%20there%20is%20a%20slight%20gradient%20that%20brightens%20the%20closer%20you%20are%20to%20the%20window.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20another%20one%20of%20those%20games%20that%20change%20the%20space%20and%20how%20we%20feel%2C%26quot%3B%20Garneau%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELeaving%20patches%20of%20exposed%20brick%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20than%20putting%20built-in%20cabinets%20everywhere%20%E2%80%94%20also%20helps%20the%20space%20breathe.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20corner%20of%20the%20living%20room%20with%20a%20cabinet%20above%20a%20small%20wooden%20desk%20with%20a%20patch%20of%20exposed%20brick.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66573b61d38d94707c2bfbb7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20desk%20in%20the%20main%20living%20space%20can%20be%20separated%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20room%20by%20a%20movable%20wall.%3Cp%3EDan%20Latu%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EExposed%20brick%20is%20visible%20above%20a%20wooden%20desk%20that%20the%20parents%20use%20as%20a%20workspace%2C%20with%20the%20gray%20built-in%20cabinets%20above%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20did%20everything%20we%20could%20to%20keep%20as%20much%20of%20it%20exposed%2C%26quot%3B%20Garneau%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20wonderful%20piece%20of%20wood%2C%20some%20brick%2C%20and%20then%20the%20grays%20with%20the%20light%20%E2%80%94%20the%20recipe%20is%20there%20for%20something%20that%20is%20soothing.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20real%20magic%20of%20the%20space%20is%20when%20the%20cabinets%20'fold'%20to%20create%20an%20additional%20bedroom.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Robert%20Garneau%20begins%20to%20swing%20open%20one%20of%20the%20gray%20walls.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66573b63f5084fadb175bd1c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C