5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%20this%20photo%20released%20by%20the%20Russian%20Defense%20Ministry%20Press%20Service%20on%20April%2015%2C%202024%2C%20Russian%20soldiers%20participate%20in%20a%20military%20exercise%20somewhere%20in%20Russian-controlled%20Donetsk%20region%2C%20eastern%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6647a15d9fc063e829b283af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223391%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20this%20photo%20released%20on%20April%2015%2C%202024%2C%20Russian%20soldiers%20participate%20in%20a%20military%20exercise%20somewhere%20in%20Russia-controlled%20Donetsk%2C%20eastern%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3ERussian%20Defence%20Ministry%20Press%20Service%20via%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Russian%20military%20planner%20said%20he%20doesn't%20sleep%20well%20after%20sending%20troops%20to%20almost%20certain%20death.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20tell%20the%20men%2C%20otherwise%20they%20wouldn't%20fight%20with%20the%20hope%20of%20winning%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERussia%20is%20known%20for%20treating%20some%20of%20its%20soldiers%20as%20disposable%2C%20letting%20them%20die%20to%20make%20progress.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Russian%20soldier%20who%20plans%20offensives%20as%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20he%20finds%20it%20difficult%20sending%20men%20into%20situations%20where%20he%20knows%20they%20will%20probably%20die.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20soldier%2C%20Pavel%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.themoscowtimes.com%2F2024%2F06%2F03%2Fon-a-train-in-southern-russia-fatigued-soldiers-see-no-end-in-sight-to-war-a85283%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Moscow%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20draw%20arrows%20on%20a%20map%2C%20and%20the%20soldiers%20move%20forward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20Pavel's%20job%20is%20to%20manage%20antiaircraft%20systems%20and%20plan%20offensives.%20This%20means%20he%20sometimes%20has%20to%20send%20men%20into%20an%20attack%20knowing%20that%20they%20are%20unlikely%20to%20survive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20tell%20the%20men%2C%20otherwise%20they%20wouldn't%20fight%20with%20the%20hope%20of%20winning%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Moscow%20Times%20said%20his%20eyes%20were%20%26quot%3Bglistening%20with%20emotion%26quot%3B%20as%20he%20spoke%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20all%20this%2C%20you%20don't%20sleep%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20Russia%20is%20sending%20soldiers%20forward%20in%20these%20attacks%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20distracting%20Ukrainian%20forces%2C%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20getting%20them%20to%20send%20soldiers%20away%20from%20its%20main%20offensives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20previously%20been%20accused%20of%20treating%20its%20soldiers%20as%20highly%20disposable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-meat-wave-assaults-leave-frozen-bodies-avdiivka-ukraine-soldier-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eusing%20%26quot%3Bmeat%20wave%26quot%3B%20tactics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20Russia%20sends%20waves%20of%20men%20forward%20to%20try%20to%20overwhelm%20Ukrainian%20positions%2C%20to%20then%20allow%20better-trained%20or%20more%20elite%20soldiers%20to%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20suffered%20a%20much%20higher%20casualty%20rate%20than%20Ukraine%20in%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20said%20late%20last%20month%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-lost-1200-a-day-highest-since-war-began-intel-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E500%2C000%20Russian%20soldiers%20had%20likely%20been%20killed%20or%20wounded%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20the%20full-scale%20invasion%20began%20in%20February%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20said%20that%20Russia's%20average%20daily%20casualties%20were%201%2C200%20in%20May%2C%20the%20highest%20numbers%20so%20far%20reported%20in%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPavel%20spoke%20to%20The%20Moscow%20Times%20on%20a%20train%20near%20Ukraine's%20border.%20Some%20soldiers%20on%20the%20train%20were%20going%20to%20the%20front%20lines%2C%20while%20others%20were%20on%20a%20short%20leave%20break.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPavel%20joined%20Russia's%20military%20as%20a%20volunteer%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.themoscowtimes.com%2F2024%2F06%2F03%2Fon-a-train-in-southern-russia-fatigued-soldiers-see-no-end-in-sight-to-war-a85283%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Moscow%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20after%20hearing%20some%20of%20his%20family%20had%20been%20killed%20by%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20previously%20worked%20as%20a%20senior%20specialist%20at%20one%20of%20Russia's%20largest%20companies%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20and%20had%20asked%20for%20his%20army%20salary%20to%20be%20given%20to%20an%20orphanage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20paid%20to%20kill%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Moscow%20Times%20reported%20that%20most%20soldiers%20on%20the%20train%20were%20drinking%2C%20including%20Pavel%2C%20and%20that%20a%20fight%20almost%20broke%20out%20between%20one%20of%20the%20soldiers%20and%20another%20passenger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20soldiers%20on%20the%20train%20described%20brutal%20conditions%2C%20with%20huge%20Russian%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20young%20guys%20I%20knew%20are%20dead%2C%20they%20weren't%20even%2030%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20soldier%2C%20Yegor%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20who%20was%20on%20his%20way%20back%20to%20the%20front%20line%20showed%20a%20gunshot%20wound%20